title: anakin_skywalker
body:
One of the main characters from the [[Star Wars]] science fiction series, and the protagonist of the prequel trilogy.

Portrayed by Jake Lloyd as a child in [[Star Wars: The Phantom Menace|The Phantom Menace]], and by [[Hayden Christensen]] or his likeness otherwise (with the exception of Sebastian Shaw's one portrayal as Anakin).

He is the padawan (disciple) of [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and the master of [[Ahsoka Tano]]. While he became a hero of the Republic, Anakin's promising career was tragically ended when [[palpatine|Darth Sidious]] corrupted him into the Dark Side, being rechristened as Sith Apprentice [[Darth Vader]].

h4. See also
* [[I am your father (meme)]]
* [[It's over Anakin I have the high ground (meme)]]

title: armored_personnel_carrier
body:
A [[ground vehicle]] designed to transport [[soldier]]s and equipment into a combat zone.

APCs are fundamentally different from [[tank]]s. Generally speaking, APCs have lighter armor (still strong enough to resist bullets and shrapnel) compared to tanks. They have lighter armament because of their focused transport purpose and for the sake of mobility. Most commonly, APCs are armed with [[machine gun]]s or automatic [[grenade launcher]]s. It can either have wheels or [[caterpillar tracks]], while tanks are always tracked. Some can be amphibious.

Not only the [[military]], [[police]] tactical units also operate it. Sometimes APCs can be utilized as [[ambulance]], especially in battlefield (see post #1085064).

h4. List of APCs

* [[aavp-7a1|AAVP-7]]
* [[BTR-4 Bucephalus]]
* [[BTR-40]]
* [[BTR-60]]
* [[BTR-80]]
** [[BTR-90]] [tn]Larger version of the BTR-80 vehicle, fitted with a BMP-2 turret.[/tn]
* [[M113]]
* [[M3 half-track]]
* [[Patria Pasi]]
* [[sdkfz 251|Sd. Kfz. 251]]
* [[Stryker (afv)|]]
* [[TPz Fuchs]]

* [[Type 96 (APC)]]

title: michael_knight
body:
[spoiler][quote][i]A man... who does not exist....[/i][/quote][/spoiler]

[b]Michael Knight[/b] is a the fictional protagonist character from the American adventure and [[science fiction]] TV series [[Knight Rider]] released in the 80s. 

Played by "David Hasselhoff":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Hasselhoff , Michael is a high-tech modern crime fighter assisted by [[K.I.T.T]]., an advanced artificially intelligent, self-aware and nearly indestructible [[robot]] sports [[car]]. 

He is the primary field agent in the pilot program of his public justice organization, the Foundation for Law and Government (FLAG). 

Michael Knight is a special type of hero, a "modern [[knight]]" who avoids violence whenever possible and generally refrains from using melee weapons or firearms although he is actually a [[Vietnam War]] veteran proficient in [[martial arts]], [[close-quarters combat]] combat and the use of .38 [[revolver]]s and the [[MAC-10/11|MAC-10]] [[submachine gun]].

Michael [spoiler]was actually born Michael Arthur Long and was a LAPD detective working undercover, when he was shot in the face during a case and left for dead. Given a new face via facial reconstructive surgery by the FLAG organization, Long was resurrected as Michael Knight and deployed as their agent (as seen in the series pilot episodes).[/spoiler] 

h4. See also

* "Wikipedia article":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Knight_(Knight_Rider)_

title: kusanagi_motoko
body:
[b]Major Kusanagi Motoko[/b] is the main character of the [[Ghost In The Shell]] [[cyberpunk]] series.

Major Kusanagi is the serious and very competent squad leader of [[police|Public Security Section 9's counter-terrorist and anti-crime unit]].

The Major is a full body [[cyborg]] with short hair with long sidelocks. Her hair color changes from series to series; from blue in the original manga (and [i]Arise[/i]), black in the movies, to purple in [i]S.A.C.[/i] Her eye color also changes, being blue (movies), green or red depending on the show. She is often seen wearing a pink [[leotard]] with pink [[thighhighs]], black [[bodysuit|battle armor]], or a yellow [[police uniform|police officer's uniform]].

The Major is also an expert in systems hacking, infiltration, [[close-quarters combat]], [[martial arts]], and is extremely proficient with many types of ballistic weapons.

title: eve_online
body:
A science-fiction MMORPG developed by Icelandic company CCP Games. It is currently the only single-shard MMORPG in existence, meaning all players share a single world (called New Eden) of over 14,000 star systems, running on the gaming industry's most powerful server.

Players take control of a 'capsuleer', an augmented human (there are no alien species in the universe, with the possible exception of the reclusive Jove, who were originally humans as well, but have undergone extensive genetic modification, resulting in what is practically a new species) whose consciousness is transferred to a clone in the event of death, making the capsuleer immortal. Capsuleers travel in small capsules (hence the name) that protect them from various dangers in space, and which, in turn, are docked into larger ships, creating a conduit between the capsuleer brain and the ship systems in order to pilot the ship.

Expansions used to be issued twice a year, but towards the end of 2014, CCP Games switched to a release cycle of 4-6 weeks between expansions.

The game is (in)famous for its steep learning curve, stemming from the many opportunities and possibilities players are faced with, all of which are available from day one.

h4. External links
* "Website":http://www.eveonline.com

title: droopy_dog_(cartoon)
body:
This is a series of animated shorts from 1943 to 1958 featuring the titular [[Droopy]] character by cartoonist Tex Avery. The character would later appear in [[Who Framed Roger Rabbit]], [[Tom and Jerry]], and other shows. On Japanese TV, the Droopy shorts were aired sandwiched between Tom and Jerry shorts, so he's often imagined in association with them.

h4. See also

title: droopy
body:
[[toon (style)|Cartoon]] character created by Tex Avery, an animator who worked for [[metro-goldwyn-mayer|MGM]], first appearing in 1943.

Droopy is an [[personification|anthropomorphic]] white [[basset hound]] with droopy jowls, [[half-closed eyes]], and [[floppy ears]]. He was the protagonist in his own set of [[Droopy Dog (cartoon)|]] shorts from 1943 to 1958 by cartoonist Tex Avery, and would later make appearances in [[Who Framed Roger Rabbit]], [[Tom and Jerry]], and other shows.

On Japanese TV, the Droopy shorts were aired sandwiched between [[Tom and Jerry]] shorts, so he's often imagined in association with them.

h4. See also

To prevent the concrete from hardening during transport, the large drum carried by the truck consistently rotates to keep the concrete from settling to maintain its liquid state.

title: moana_(movie)
body:
Moana is a 2016 American animated musical fantasy adventure film produced by Walt Disney Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. The film was directed by John Musker and Ron Clements, co-directed by Chris Williams and Don Hall, and produced by Osnat Shurer, from a screenplay written by Jared Bush, and based on a story conceived by Clements, Musker, Williams, Hall, Pamela Ribon, and the writing team of Aaron Kandell and Jordan Kandell.
The film stars [[the rock (dwayne johnson)|Dwayne Johnson]] and Auliʻi Cravalho in her film debut as the voice of [[moana waialiki|the eponymous character]] and also features the voices of Rachel House, Temuera Morrison, Jemaine Clement, Nicole Scherzinger, and Alan Tudyk. It features original songs written by Lin-Manuel Miranda, Opetaia Foa'i, and Mark Mancina, and an original musical orchestral score also composed by Mancina. The film is set in ancient Polynesia and tells the story of Moana, the strong-willed daughter of a chief of a coastal village, who is chosen by the ocean itself to reunite a mystical relic with the goddess Te Fiti. When a blight strikes her island, Moana sets sail in search of Maui, a legendary demigod, in hopes of returning the relic to Te Fiti and saving her people. The screenplay takes inspiration from Polynesian myths.

title: moana_waialiki
body: Moana of Motunui is the title character of the 2016 Walt Disney Animation Studios film [[Moana (movie)|]]. Created by directors Ron Clements and John Musker, Moana is voiced by Hawaiian actress and singer Auliʻi Cravalho. As a toddler, she is voiced by Louise Bush. Moana returns in the sequel film Moana 2, which premiered in November of 2024, again voiced by Cravalho, as well as a live-action remake film, in 2026, in which she will be portrayed by Catherine Laga'aia.

title: maui_(moana)
body: Maui is a demigod of South Pacific legends. Despite his status, Maui finds himself torn between the worlds of humanity and deity, feeling "stuck in the middle". Nevertheless, he finds enjoyment in showcasing his godlike abilities to others.

title: kogal
body:
[b]Kogal[/b] (コギャル), a substyle of [[Gyaru]] (ギャル), is a [[fashion]] trend among young female Japanese high school students.

They follow the trends of gyaru fashion in their heavy makeup (especially around the eyes), sometimes [[tan]] skin, use of English-influenced slang (kogyarugo or コギャル語), coloured (and often bleached) hair, and trendy gyaru style fashion. Since they are school girls, they use their [[school uniform]] as their fashion statement, often wearing their uniform skirts very short and paired with [[loose socks]].

If there aren't any obvious signs of kogal (school uniform, [[loose socks]], [[scrunchie]], etc) then it's recommended to just tag the image with the more general [[gyaru]].

Beck, and first appeared in the debut issue of Fawcett Comics' The Marvel Family comic book in December 1945. Since DC Comics licensed and acquired Fawcett's characters in the 1970s, Black Adam has endured as one of the most popular archenemies of the superhero [[shazam|Captain Marvel / Shazam]] and the Marvel Family alongside Doctor Sivana and Mister Mind.

title: dayflower
body:
[b][i]Commelina[/i][/b], commonly called dayflower, is a genus of [[flower]]ing plants in the family [i]Commelinaceae[/i]. Commonly represented by [i]Commelina communis[/i] (Asiatic dayflower), native to East and Southeast Asia.

Commelinas are small flowers that are usually blue, but they also come in shades of white, yellow, purple, and pink. The flowers emerge from a boat-like sheath called a spathe that surrounds the flower stem.  Common species, such as the Asiatic dayflower, have a distinctive appearance: The flowers appear to have only two petals at the top, but there is actually a third, inconspicuous white petal at the bottom. They also have a distinctive pistil and stamens that curve upward.

h4. Examples

title: tatara_kogasa
body:
The "Cheery Forgotten Umbrella". 

Stage 2 mid-boss and boss, as well as Extra Stage mid-boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Undefined Fantastic Object]][/i], and Stage 3 mid-boss of [i][[Ten Desires]][/i]. A [i]karakasa[/i] youkai who frequently tries (in vain) to surprise humans. She carries her [[purple umbrella|purple]] [[karakasa obake]] with a [[tongue]] almost always sticking out, although there is some debate as to whether the girl or the umbrella (or both) is the real Kogasa. Fanworks often depict her under the mercy of [[Kochiya Sanae]] due to the latter's scathing words against her back in UFO.

Due to similarities in her style of dress to [[Kazami Yuuka]] (designated by [[ZUN (artist)|]] as "youkai moe"), along with her being perceived as a highly moe character in her own right, Kogasa is often referred to by fans as "the new youkai moe."

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24008618
* !asset #24008619

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blue hair]] and [[heterochromia]] with [[blue eyes|blue]] and [[red eyes]]. She wears a [[white shirt]] with [[juliet sleeves]], a [[blue vest]], a [[blue skirt]], and [[geta]]. In [[Wild and Horned Hermit]] she wears a [[frilled capelet|frilled]] [[blue capelet]] instead of her vest. 

h4. See also

* Pool #2555 - Surprise!  For instances where she actually manages to surprise someone.
* [[Urameshiya]], Kogasa's catchphrase
* [[List of Touhou Characters]]

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Kogasa Tatara":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Kogasa_Tatara
* "Wikipedia: Kasa-obake":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kasa-obake

title: wicker_man
body:
An ancient celtic druidic means of sacrifice, a large effigy in the shape of a man is built out of straw, where the condemned or simply slaves are put within and set ablaze.
The only known source of the wicker man's existence is from the writings of Gaius Julius Caesar and earlier writings by Posidonius the historian.

For the Noble Phantasm wielded by [[Cu Chulainn (Caster) (fate)|]] in [[Fate/Grand Order]], use [[Wicker Man (fate)]].

title: tennis_no_ouji-sama
body:
A [[tennis]]-themed sports (and action) manga and anime series written and illustrated by [[Konomi Takeshi]]. It was serialized in [[Weekly Shounen Jump]] from 1999 to 2008. Localized as [b]The Prince of Tennis[/b] outside Japan.

The series is famous for an absurd amount of violence that is best compared to martial arts manga, with superhuman abilities, special moves, and life-threatening injuries. This unusual approach of sports manga is intentional on behalf of Konomi, who wanted it to be a departure from other popular sports manga and anime series at that time.

title: witness_holes
body:
"The term 'witness holes' generally refers to the small openings on the back or side-face of a handgun magazine allowing operators to visually confirm how many cartridges are loaded. Most modern semi-automatic handguns come standard with magazines featuring witness holes. It may also refer to the hole drilled in the top of a pistol barrel chamber so a user may visually confirm if there is a round chambered. This serves as a type of loaded-chamber indicator (LCI) but has no mechanical parts and does not allow for confirmation in low-light conditions when compared to a traditional LCI."

—SIG Sauer Glossary https://www.sigsauer.com/glossary/witness-holes/

title: halberd
body:
A popular and versatile [[polearm]]. Its main distinguishing features are a head consisting of an [[axe]] blade, a [[spear]]head, and a hook or angled spike opposite the axe.

While the term halberd refers specifically to the medieval/renaissance European polearm, similar polearms such as the knightly poleaxe/pollaxe and Chinese [[qinglong ji]] also fall under this category.

Not to be confused with [[Meta Knight|Meta Knight's]] [[halberd_(airship)|signature battleship]].

title: light_fixture
body:
Also known as a Luminaire, a light Fixture is a device that holds a light source. 

While  usually permanent, they differ from light Fittings, as Fixtures aren't fused to the building they're on, and can usually be swapped out.

Light fixtures examples: Desk Lamps,  ceiling fans lights, LED exit signs, fluorescent light fixtures, ceiling Strip lights

title: let_me_solo_her
body:
Also known as [b]Klein Tsuboi[/b], a legendary [[Elden Ring]] [[tarnished (elden ring)|player]] with a summon sign outside [[malenia blade of miquella|Malenia]]'s boss fight.  Fights naked except for a [[pot on head|pot on their head]].  As his name suggests, is capable of soloing a co-op boosted Malenia without assistance from the summoner.

A screenshot of "this":[https://www.reddit.com/r/Eldenring/comments/u22zpa/heres_to_an_absolute_legend_let_me_solo_her/] particular Reddit post started the legend, and a screenshot of it shared outside of the website made it popular overrall.

On May 10th, 2022, Let Me Solo Her has soloed Malenia for the 1000th time.

With the release of [[Elden Ring: Shadow of the Erdtree]], they changed their player name to Let Me Solo Them, facing the DLC's most challenging boss, [spoiler][[Promised Consort Radahn]][/spoiler].

h4. See also

* "Youtube Video":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IqN2phpMWno]

title: hindenburg_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the German heavy cruiser [i]Hindenburg[/i], as part of a collaboration with [[World of Warships]]. 
Character design by [[Yunsang]], voiced by [[Matsui Eriko]].

She has [[absurdly long hair|absurdly long]] [[red hair]] with [[ahoge]] and [[hair intakes]], [[red eyes]], [[large breasts]], [[pointy ears]], [[demon wings]], and [[demon tail|tail]]. Her outfit consists of a black [[crop top]] exposing her [[underboob]]s, [[pleated dress|pleated]] [[black dress]], [[black pantyhose]], [[black footwear|black]] [[thigh boots]], and a [[black hairband]]. Her [[rigging]] consists of two of her four planned 203 mm triple gun mounts on a dragon-like automaton. 

The fourth shipgirl introduced as part of the sixth wave of Priority Ships, [i]Hindenburg[/i] is basically an upscaled version of [[Roon (Azur Lane)|]], using the same 203 mm triple mounts, but her hull is based off the [i]Admiral Hipper[/i]-class to accommodate an extra fourth gun mount and four 533 mm quad [[torpedo tubes]]. Another note is that her size and displacement is similar to a battleship.

h4. Skins

* !post #6489487: Default
* !post #7005180: [[Hindenburg (Delirious Duel) (Azur Lane)|Delirious Duel]]

title: e3_tsubasa
body:
The E3 series (E3系) is a Japanese [[Shinkansen]] [[high-speed train]] type built for Komachi services which commenced on 3 June 1997, coinciding with the opening of the new Akita Shinkansen "mini-shinkansen" line, a regular line between Morioka and Akita re-gauged to 1,435 mm (4 ft 8+1⁄2 in) standard gauge. Later versions of the E3 series were also introduced for use on Yamagata Shinkansen Tsubasa services. Both "mini-shinkansen" lines join the Tohoku Shinkansen, providing services to and from Tokyo.

title: wrecking_crew
body:
A 1985 puzzle game released for the [[NES|Nintendo Entertainment System]] and the second [i]Wrecking Crew[/i] game. It's based on the arcade game of the similar name that released a year prior, [i]Vs. Wrecking Crew[/i], but focuses more on a single player puzzle game aspect than the competitive multiplayer of it's arcade counterpart. 

[[Mario]] & [[Luigi]] are demolition men who are tasked to destroy all the breakable walls in a given level to clear the stage (called "Phases"). They must find a way to accomplish this while navigating the roaming monsters hot on their tail, frequent fireballs spawning and a rival demolition man [[Foreman_spike|Spike]] trying to break the wall they're near to knock them down.

A stage based on this game was added to [i][[Super Smash Bros.]] for Wii U[/i].

title: daicon_iii
body:
An animated short for the 20th Annual Japan National SF Convention, also known as [b]Daicon III[/b], held in 1981 in Osaka, Japan. 

It was created by a studio formed in the early 1980s called [[Daicon]] Film. Daicon film would eventually become [[Gainax]] Studio a few years later.

While this animated short was ambitious, its animation was rough and low-quality.

[b]"The opening for Daicon III":http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CQjruwkyOaU
[/b]

* [[Daicon Bunny Girl]]

title: csx_corporation
body:
CSX Corporation is an American holding company focused on rail transportation and real estate in North America.  Their subsidiary CSX Transportation is a freight railroad operating in the eastern United States and the Canadian provinces of [[Ontario]] and [[Quebec|Québec]].

CSX and its chief competitor, the Norfolk Southern Railway, have a duopoly on the transcontinental freight rail lines in the Northeastern and Southern United States

title: poutine
body:
A dish of [[french fries]] and cheese curds topped with a brown [[gravy]].  It emerged in [[Quebec|Québec]], [[Canada]] in the 1950's, though it's exact origin remains unknown.  It since gained popularity in the rest of Canada becoming a national comfort food.

In the US a similar dish called Disco Fries exists, originating from the US state of New Jersey.  The primary difference between it and poutine is that it is made using shredded mozzarella cheese instead cheese curds.  The dish's exact origin date is unknown, but it was named in the 1970's after the late night customers coming in from disco clubs.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Poutine":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poutine]

title: praying_mantis
body:
A [[bug]] in the Mantidae family, having long bodies and fore-limbs closed together in a prayer-like stance, hence their name. Mantises protect themselves with camouflage, and some species spread their wings and forearms in a threatening stance.

title: tuatara
body: Tuatara (Sphenodon punctatus) are reptiles endemic to New Zealand. Although resembling most [[lizard]]s, they are part of a distinct lineage, the order Rhynchocephalia. Their name derives from the Māori language, and means "peaks on the back". The single species of tuatara is the sole surviving member of its order, which originated in the Triassic period around 250 million years ago and which flourished during the Mesozoic era.

title: turtle
body:
[b]Turtles[/b] are reptiles famed for their slow pace, longevity and [[shell]]s. Most turtles are able to retract into their shells for protection.

Turtles are occasionally depicted as [[oversized animal|massive]] in size, sometimes [[island turtle|large enough]] to carry [[city|cities]], or even worlds.

title: plumeria_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Plumeria[/b], known as [b]Plumeri[/b] (プルメリ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]][/i].

This [[Team Skull]] Admin controls the rest of the team and is seen as something of a big sister type. She looks after the Grunts and won't forgive anyone who bullies them.

She has [[yellow eyes]] with [[eyeshadow]] and [[long hair|long]] [[two-tone hair|two-tone]] [[pink hair|pink]] and [[blonde hair|yellow hair]] worn in [[quad tails]]. She wears a [[skull hair ornament]] and [[skull necklace|necklace]], a [[tank top]] which reveals a [[stomach tattoo]] on her [[midriff]], and [[black pants]].

h4. Official Art

title: sophocles_(pokemon)
body:
Sophocles is a character introduced in [[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]]. He is one of Alola's Trial Captains, specializing in the Electric type. In Sophocles' trial, the player battles a Totem [[Vikavolt]]. In [[pokemon usum|Ultra Sun and Ultra Moon]], they fight a Totem [[Togedemaru]] instead.

Sophocles inherited the position of captain from his cousin, [[Molayne (pokemon)|]], who he shares a close bond with. He is into mechanics, having invented various machines, and is the founder of the Festival Plaza. However, he is quite shy, and afraid of the dark. [spoiler]Sophocles is one of the trainers who can challenge the player for the title of Champion.[/spoiler]

In the [[pokemon (anime)|anime]], Sophocles is also one of [[ash ketchum|Ash]]'s classmates. He is a intelligent but shy boy who became fascinated with space at a young age.

Japanese name: [b]Maamane[/b]

title: hogwarts_school_uniform
body:
The [[school uniform]] design from the [[Harry Potter (series)|]] series, worn by students at the Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.

The uniform typically consists of a [[grey sweater]] or [[cardigan]] over a white [[dress shirt]] and black [[pants]] or a [[black skirt]]. A black [[hooded cloak]] goes over their clothes. Both the inner lining of the cloak and the [[necktie]] and various accessories will be in the student's house color.

Back in the late 19th century, when [[Hogwarts Legacy]] happens, the uniform had [[plaid pants]] for the boys and [[long skirt|long]] [[plaid skirt]]s for the girls.

h4. House colors
* [[Gryffindor]]: red and gold
* [[Ravenclaw]]: blue and grey
* [[Hufflepuff]]: yellow and black
* [[Slytherin]]: green and silver

h4.See also

* [[List of Uniforms]]

title: ajinomoto
body:
Japanese multinational food and chemical corporation, most well-known internationally for its [[monosodium glutamate]] (MSG) product, from which the company derives its name, Aji-No-Moto (literally "essence of taste").  Alongside MSG and other condiments/seasonings, the company also produces processed foods such as instant noodles (ala [[instant ramen]] and pasta) and instant soups, frozen foods, coffees, cooking oils, TV dinners, sweeteners, amino acids and pharmaceuticals, among other things. In particular it is the world's largest producer of aspartame, with a 40% global market share.

They also produce [[Knorr (brand)|]]-branded products in Japan under license.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia article":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajinomoto

A strong—willed veteran with a penchant for battling, this member of the Elite Four tries to wear opponents down. She seems to have some history with Professor Oak [tn](official bio)[/tn]. Her signature Pokémon is [[Gengar]].

In her [[pokemon frlg|FRLG]] outfit, she has [[black eyes]] and [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[flipped hair|flipped]] [[blonde hair]] with [[parted bangs]]. She wears a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[purple dress|dress]] with a [[pearl (gemstone)|pearl]], a [[white apron|white]] [[waist apron|apron]], [[brown pantyhose]], [[purple footwear|purple]] [[shoes]], and a [[cane]].

title: bruno_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Bruno[/b], known as [b]Siba[/b] (シバ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rgby|Red and Green]][/i].

A member of the Elite Four who believes that people and Pokémon can become stronger though rigorous—even extreme—training, he shouts "Hoo Hah!" to get fired up [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His signature Pokémon is [[Machamp]].

He is [[muscular male|muscular]], has [[black eyes]], and [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] tied in a [[ponytail]] with [[long sideburns]]. He is [[topless male|shirtless]] and wears [[bracelet]]s, a [[black belt|black cloth]] [[belt]], [[torn pants|torn]] [[white pants]], [[anklet]]s, and is [[barefoot]].

title: blaine_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Blaine[/b], known as [b]Katsura[/b] (カツラ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rgby|Red and Green]][/i].

This old man with a passion for trivia is known as the hotheaded quiz master. He's a Fire-type Gym Leader with a veteran Trainer's skill and a researcher's knowledge [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His signature Pokémon is [[Arcanine]].

In his [[pokemon frlg|FRLG]] outfit, he is [[old man|old]], [[bald]], and has a [[white hair|white]] [[mustache]]. He wears [[round eyewear|round]] [[sunglasses]], a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[grey shirt|shirt]], an [[orange necktie|orange]] [[poke ball print|print]] necktie, a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[lab coat]], [[purple pants|pants]] with a [[belt buckle|buckled]] [[black belt|belt]], and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]].

title: giovanni_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Giovanni[/b], known as [b]Sakaki[/b] (サカキ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rgby|Red and Green]][/i], serving as the series' recurring and main antagonist.

This leader of the expansive Team Rainbow Rocket enterprise, which aims to use Pokémon to rule the world, believes Pokémon are no more than tools [tn](official bio)[/tn]. His signature Pokémon is [[Rhyperior]].

He has [[black eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]]. He wears a [[grey shirt|grey]] [[turtleneck]] shirt under a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[v-neck]] [[black jacket]] which has the Team Rocket [[logo]] emblazoned on the front, [[black pants]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]].

title: lana_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Lana[/b], known as [b]Suiren[/b] (スイレン) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon sm|Sun and Moon]][/i].

Lana is an avid fisher and one of the captains of Akala Island. She loves her family and is constantly helping the family business or babysitting her twin sisters [tn](official bio)[/tn]. Her signature Pokémon is [[Araquanid]].

She has [[blue eyes]] with [[bright pupils|bright]] [[white pupils|pupils]] and [[no sclera]], [[short hair|short]] [[blue hair]], and [[freckles]]. She wears a [[yellow hairband|hairband]], a [[one-piece swimsuit|swimsuit]] [[swimsuit under clothes|under]] a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[white shirt|shirt]] with a [[blue sailor collar|blue collar]], [[blue pants|blue]] [[wave print]] [[capri pants|pants]], and [[flip-flops]].

title: frankenstein's_monster
body:
A monster created by Dr. [[Victor Frankenstein]] by unspecified means.

Most modern depictions of Frankenstein's monster are based on the "1931 adaptation":https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0021884/, in which the monster was stitched together from parts of corpses and animated by electricity from a lightning storm. Monsters based on this film tend to have angular features, prominent [[stitches]], and [[bolt (hardware)|bolts]] drilled into the head or neck. Later depictions from the era of color film gave the monster [[grey_skin|grey]] or [[green skin]].

h4. See also

* [[Frankenstein]]
* [[golem]]
* [[monster]]
* [[undead]]
* [[Tag Group:Legendary Creatures]]
other_names: フランケンシュタインの怪物

title: amelie_planchard
body:
Character from [[Strike Witches: Katayoku no Majo-tachi]]

A Sergeant from Gallia serving in the [[Isle of Wight Detachment Group]]. A very shy and crybaby girl, known for her crush on [[Perrine H. Clostermann]], and for being [[Wilma Bishop]]'s girltoy.

Her weapon is a Bren Light Machine gun Mk 1. Her familiar is a European rabbit, and she's based on Henri Planchard.
other_names: アメリー・プランシャール

title: luciana_mazzei
body:
Character from [[Strike Witches: Kurenai no Majo-tachi]].

A Pilot Officer from Romagna serving in the [[504th Joint Fighter Wing]], Ardor Witches. Member of the Pantaloni Rossi trio with [[Fernandia Malvezzi]] and [[Martina Crespi]].
Her familiar is a greyhound, her weapons are the anti-tank rifles Solothurn S-18/1000 and Boys, and she's based on Pietro Mazzei.
other_names: ルチアナ・マッツェイ

title: javanese_text
body:
Posts that contain text written in Javanese, either in Latin or its own Javanese script.

The Javanese language is an Austronesian language. It is spoken mostly on [[Java]], in [[Indonesia]].
Its closest relatives include [[sundanese_text|Sundanese]], [[madurese_text|Madurese]] and [[balinese_text|Balinese]] with [[malay_text|Malay]] and, therefore, [[indonesian_text|Indonesian]] being its distant relatives.

h4. See also

* [[Tag group:Text]]

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Javanese language":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javanese_language
* "Wikipedia: Javanese script":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javanese_script

title: tiny_green_mall_wizard
body:
[b]Tiny Green Mall Wizard[/b], also known as the Wizard Gnome, is a character created by TikToker "crawly_possessed" with which he dresses in a fake white beard, green robes and a white cone-shaped hat while crawling through stores in a mall. The TikToker previously went viral for the Crawling In Public trend in which he invited his followers to come crawl through a mall in Warsaw, Poland with him. The creator posted his first video as the Tiny Green Mall Wizard in late June 2024.

Since then Crawly has engaged in racism, hate speech, staged vandalism, real vandalism and overall aggressive behavior which coupled with his earlier harassment of mall workers earned him rightful bans on both TikTok and Kick. On November 29th 2024 he was apprehended by Polish Border Guard to begin a deportation procedure.

title: goomboss
body:
Boss character introduced in [i][[Paper Mario 64]][/i], and later incorporated into [i][[Super Mario 64 DS]][/i] and [i][[Mario Kart DS]][/i]. 

Formerly known as the [b]Goomba King[/i], he is a large [[Goomba]] with a [[crown]], crazy [[ringed eyes]] and red-and-white [[striped pants]]. He has large, distinctive singular white [[facial hair]] on each side of his face.

title: madame_clairvoya
body:
A portrait ghost to be captured in [i][[Luigi's Mansion]][/i]. 

Known as the [b]Freaky-Fortune Teller[/b], she can tell the future by connecting with the spirit world and peering into her crystal ball. If [[Luigi]] brings her [[Mario]]'s lost items she will slowly uncover his whereabouts and the secrets of the mansion.

Her notable trademarks are having [[long_hair|long]] [[white hair]], [[blue skin]], and [[glowing_eyes|glowing]] [[yellow eyes]] that [[solid_eyes|lack pupils]]. She wears a [[red dress]], a [[gold necklace]] and big [[hoop_earrings|earrings]]. Both her head and her [[mouth_veil|mouth]] are covered in [[purple veil]]s.

She is the only Portrait Ghost who is not an enemy and volunteers to be captured, as she apparently prefers the "peace" of being in the painting.

title: kaenbyou_rin
body:
The "Traffic Accident of Hell". Stage 4 mid-boss, Stage 5 mid-boss and boss and Stage 6 mid-boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Subterranean Animism]][/i]. Also known as "Orin" (お燐) to differentiate her from the earlier, concept-only character [[Satsuki Rin]].

A [i]kasha[/i] (monster [[cat girl|cat]]) responsible for transporting corpses on her [[wheelbarrow]] to the Hell of Blazing Fires to regulate its heat. Having learned of [[Reiuji Utsuho]]'s new power and her naive ambition to conquer the surface world, and fearing punishment from their master [[Komeiji Satori]], Rin sent evil spirits above the ground to warn any able fighter to face this threat. Apparent master of the so-called "[[zombie fairy (touhou)|Zombie Fairies]]". Occasionally depicted as a necrophiliac. She appears to have befriended [[Chen]] in [[Foul Detective Satori]], and passed her talent for finding and retrieving dead bodies to her.

h4. Appearance
* !post #6586882

She has both [[cat ears|cat]] [[extra ears|and]] [[pointy ears|human-ish ears]], [[red hair]] in [[twin braids]] tied with [[black bow|black]] [[hair bow]]s, [[blunt bangs|blunted bangs]], and [[two tails|two]] [[cat tail]]s. Her outfit is a [[green dress|green]] or [[black dress]] with either [[puffy short sleeves]] or [[juliet sleeves]] but almost [[frilled dress|always]] [[frilled sleeves|frilled]], a [[black ribbon|black]] [[leg ribbon]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]]. Often accompanied by her [[floating skull|floating]] and [[flaming skull]]s.

Her [[kaenbyou rin (cat)|cat form]] is as a [[black cat]] with [[two tails]], occasionally [[flame-tipped tail|flame-tipped]].
h4. See also

* "Nyan Clan of Gensokyo":/pools/17046

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Rin Kaenbyou":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Rin_Kaenbyou

body:

A colossal [[Piranha Plant]] that isn't rooted to the ground but is able to walk freely, making it much more similar to that of a [[Ptooie]] or [[Trottin' Piranha Plant]].

title: captain_syrup
body:
[[Wario Land]] character and the main antagonist of [i][[Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3]][/i] and [i][[Wario Land II]][/i]. 

Leader of the Black Sugar Gang pirates. She steals treasure from all around the world and hordes her ill-begotten gains in Syrup Castle, located on Kitchen Island.

In her appearances in [i]Wario Land: Super Mario Land 3[/i] and [i]Wario Land II[/i], she's seen wearing a cyan one-piece outfit with yellow sashes throughout. In her reappearance in [i][[Wario Land: Shake It!]][/i], she's been given a purple top and bandana, black pants and a red skull belt with it.

h4. Official Art

* !post #1311418: [[Wario Land: Shake It!]]

title: instant_loss
body:
Images themed on the "almost comically instant loss" situations. Often used with [[mating press]] and [[chinpo ni wa katenakatta yo]]. Though not all instant loss post involves sexual engagements.

This tag does not necessarily have to follow the [[2koma]] format, and can apply to two separately uploaded posts, so long as they depict a series of sequential events.

"Pixiv Encyclopedia":http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E5%8D%B3%E5%A0%95%E3%81%A12%E3%82%B3%E3%83%9E%E3%82%B7%E3%83%AA%E3%83%BC%E3%82%BA said that it started as a personal webcomic series by a certain artist. After that, however, the original webcomics were deleted for some reason. The series name is now used as a general tag on pixiv.

[b]Note:[/b] Just because a post depicts an SFW scene followed by an NSFW scene, it doesn't necessarily mean it's an "instant loss" situation.

h4. Examples

h5. Safe for work

* !post #6318363
* !post #8423637
* !post #5417822
* !post #3973464

h5. Not safe for work

* post #8445947
* post #8428112
* post #7796593
* post #8422909

title: floette_(eternal)
body:
Eternal Flower Floette, a special form of [[Floette]].

Key characteristics:

* Blue underside and eyelashes
* Red rings around its ears
* It holds a red flower with 6 petals (3 large and 3 small)

[[az_(pokemon)|AZ]]'s Eternal Flower Floette has a role in the story of [i][[pokemon_xy|Pokémon XY]][/i]. Additionally, Eternal Flower Floette exists in the game data as a normal Pokémon with its base stat total being 1 less than that of [[Florges]], but it is not obtainable by any means.

title: pizza_tower
body:
Indie video game inspired by the [[Wario Land]] and [[Jazz Jackrabbit]] series, in development by [[McPig]] since 2018, released in 2023.

Features [[Peppino Spaghetti]] climbing the titular tower, with the aid of [[Gustavo (pizza tower)|]] & [[Brick (pizza tower)|]]. Each level features a set of five Toppins to collect ([[Mushroom Toppin (pizza tower)|Mushroom]], [[Cheese Toppin (pizza tower)|Cheese]], [[Tomato Toppin (pizza tower)|Tomato]], [[Sausage Toppin (pizza tower)|Sausage]], and [[Pineapple Toppin (pizza tower)|Pineapple]]) and [[Gerome (pizza tower)|]] the Janitor. Each floor of the tower features several levels, ending with reaching [[Pillar John]] and rushing back to the start, and a boss fight, going up against [[Pepperman]], [[The Vigilante]], [[The Noise]], [spoiler][[Fake Peppino]][/spoiler], and [[Pizzaface]] respectively, with each boss being accessed after collecting a certain amount of Toppins and paying [[Mr. Stick (pizza tower)|]] for access. Each level has relatively distinct themes and gimmicks, with some reoccurring elements, including enemies such as [[Forknight]]s or [[Stupid Rat (pizza tower)|]]s. Each floor has at least one secret room in the hub area, one featuring the Noise's girlfriend, [[Noisette (pizza tower)|]]. 

The second floor features the level Fun Farm, which involves special guest [[Mort (mort the chicken)|Mort the Chicken]] from the 2000 PS1 game of the [[mort the chicken|same name]], who is prominently featured in that level's title card. This inspired a wave of title card art featuring Peppino crossing over with various other properties.

title: james_bond
body:
The main character of the [[james bond (series)|James Bond series]]. He is a secret agent for the [[england|British]] Secret Intelligence Service (MI6) as part of their double-o agents program (thus his codename - 007).

Throughout the James Bond movies, the character has been played by several actors including [[Sean Connery]] (1962–1967, 1971, 1983), David Niven (1967), George Lazenby (1969), Roger Moore (1973–1985), Timothy Dalton (1987–1989), Pierce Brosnan (1995–2002) and [[Daniel Craig]] (2006–2021).

title: paloma_(james_bond)
body: [b]Paloma[/b] ([b]"Dove"[/b]) is a fictional female character from [[James Bond (series)]]. She first appeared in the [[No Time To Die]] film from 2021 and is played by [[Ana de Armas]].

title: massachusetts
body: The Commonwealth of Massachusetts is a state in the New England region of the [[United States]] of America. It was one of the first thirteen states in the Union, with the official history going back to 1620 during the foundation of the Plymouth Colony. The Commonwealth of Massachusetts is home to over seven million people and the capital and most populous city is [[Boston]].

title: wardrobe_malfunction
body:
Failure of an article of clothing, such as a bra slipping or fabric tearing, that exposes some or all of one's private parts.

Not to be confused with [[accidental exposure]], in which the article of clothing does not fail, nor does the person wear it incorrectly, but they are exposed by some external factor, such as [[wind lift]].

Amusingly, the phrase was originally coined as a public relations fig leaf for what was really a case of [[assisted exposure]].

h4. See also

* [[accidental exposure]]
* [[assisted exposure]]
* [[dressing]] / [[undressing]]
* [[nipple slip]]
* [[one breast out]]
* [[popped button]]
* [[torn clothes]]
** [[tearing clothes]]
* [[wardrobe error]] - for when clothes are worn incorrectly, but not malfunctioning
* [[oversized clothes]] / [[undersized clothes]]
* [[unlikely accident]]

title: star_wars:_the_phantom_menace
body:
[b]Star Wars: Episode I – The Phantom Menace[/b] is a 1999 American epic space opera film written and directed by [[George Lucas]]. It is the fourth film in the [[Star Wars]] film series, the first film of the prequel trilogy and the first in chronological order.

Set 32 years before the original trilogy, (13 years before the formation of the Galactic Empire), during the era of the Galactic Republic, the plot follows Jedi Master [[Qui-Gon Jinn]] and his apprentice [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] as they try to protect Queen [[Padme Amidala]] of Naboo in hopes of securing a peaceful end to an interplanetary trade dispute. Joined by [[Anakin Skywalker]]—a young [[slave]] with unusually strong natural powers of the Force—they simultaneously contend with the mysterious return of the [[Sith]]. 

The film was produced by Lucasfilm and distributed by [[20th century studios|20th Century Fox]].
 [[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones|Attack of the Clones]] (2002) and [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith|Revenge of the Sith]] (2005) followed The Phantom Menace, rounding out the Star Wars prequel trilogy.

title: hairpin
body:
A [[hair ornament]] used to hold hair in place. Unlike a [[hairclip]], a hairpin lacks a clasping mechanism and simply slides into the hair. It can take the shape of a 'U' or a [[hair stick|stick]] and may have decorative ornaments at one end. The simplest and the most common hairpin is a bobby pin, which is often drawn as a simple line on a lock of hair.

h4. See also

* [[hairclip]]
* [[hair stick]]
* [[chinese hairpin]]

title: nissan
body:
A major Japanese [[car|automobile]] company founded in 1933. Operated in export markets under the [[Datsun]] marque until 1984. In 1989 they opened [[Infiniti (company)|]] to sell their luxury vehicles in America under new branding.

title: mint_(arknights)
body:
[i]Mint, the Victorian Caster, seeks recognition as a scholar far more than as a Caster.[/i]

A playable Caster Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real name: Eleanor.

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]
[tbody]
      [tr][td]Place of Birth:[/td]
      [td]Victoria[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Birthday:[/td]
      [td]February 5[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Race:[/td]
      [td]Feline[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Height:[/td]
      [td]155 cm[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Combat Experience:[/td]
      [td]None[/td][/tr]
  [/tbody]
[/table]
[/expand]

Affiliated with the Victorian Institution for Higher Studies, specializing in geology, frequently participating in investigative field projects. She contracted Oripathy on an expedition and was referred by Operator [[Skyfire (Arknights)|]] to Rhodes Island for consultation and eventual treatment.

Has a serious sense of curiosity which has frequently put her in danger. Also in possession of a monster book and a staff, which she uses during combat.

Her motif is based on [[Siamese cat|Siamese cats]].

Her [[voice actor]] is [[Oowada Hitomi]].

h4. Skins

* [[Mint (Tsukiyoi) (arknights)|Tsukiyoi]]
* [[Mint (Private Study) (Arknights)|Private Study]]

title: tantou
body:
A single or double-edged [[short sword]] or [[dagger]] carried by [[samurai]] in Japan or by noblewomen for self-defense. The sides of the blade are nearly flat.

Early tantous had no aesthetic quality and were pure weapons, but up until the 16th century, the tanto was preferred to the [[wakizashi]] for use in battle by samurai while a wakizashi was used for ceremonial occasions. After this period, they were used interchangeably. Can be used either for stabbing or slashing.

h4. See also

The 3rd season of the [[Bakugan]] anime series, which centers around the war between the alien races known as Neathians and the Gundalians.

[[kuusou_danma|Kuso Dan]], [[Marukura Marucho]] and [[Kazami Shun]] return as the main 3 recurring brawlers, and are joined by [[Fabia Sheen]], [[Jake Vallory]] and [[Ren Krawler]].

The main Gundalian antagonists are the 12 Orders who are lead by Emperor Barodius. The initial antagonists are Gundalian agents sent to Earth, which are comprised of [[Bruce Brown]], [[Ethan Glenn]], [[Lena Isis]], [[Sid Arkail]] and [[Zenet Sirone]].

body:

In the story, she and [[Marcus (Reverse:1999)|Marcus]] are off to Vienna to find clues about Manus Vindictae's ritual that makes them immune to the Storm. Thanks to the joint effort of her, Marcus, and [[Kakania (Reverse:1999)|Kakania]], their mission is success [spoiler]making her sacrifice all worth it.[/spoiler]

Her family name, Hofmann, become the base name of the ritual core against the "Storm", [[Hofmann Knot]].

She is voiced by Marisa McIntyre in English and [[Taichi You]] in Japanese.

title: commander_cody
body: Character from [[Star Wars]], Cody, formerly designated CC-2224, was a male Clone Marshal Commander in the Grand Army of the Republic who commanded the 7th Sky Corps—including its renowned subunit the 212th Attack Battalion—during the Clone Wars. He served as the second-in-command of High [[Jedi]] General [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] within the Third Systems Army and the 7th Sky Corps. General Kenobi found the commander to be reliable, trustworthy and loyal, with his abilities as a soldier and strategist earning Cody the respect of both his Jedi superiors and fellow clone troopers.

title: b'omarr_monk
body:
The B'omarr Order, which consisted of B'omarr monks, was a religious order that believed in isolating themselves from all physical sensation to enhance the power of their minds. To that aim, enlightened monks had their brains transplanted into nutrient-filled jars. Whenever they wanted to move, those bottled-brains used spider-like droid walkers. Older monks used four-legged walkers, but younger monks used a six-legged variant.

The order possessed multiple regeneration gems, which at the time of [[Jabba the Hutt]] were stored underground behind triple doors.

The B'omarr Order first appeared in the 1983 film [[star wars: return of the jedi|Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi]].

title: train_station_platform_gate
body:
Also Known As Platform screen doors (PSDs), & Platform edge doors (PEDs), are used at some [[train station|train]], rapid transit and people mover stations to separate the platform from [[Railroad tracks|train tracks]], as well as on some [[bus]] rapid transit, [[streetcar|tram]] and light rail systems. Primarily used for passenger safety, they are a relatively new addition to many [[Subway|metro]] systems around the world, some having been retrofitted to established systems. They are widely used in newer Asian and European metro systems, and Latin American bus rapid transit systems.

title: deadpool
body:
[i]I always forget (or just black out to spare myself the agony) what Wilson's most [b]lethal weapon[/b] is... his [b]mouth![/b] He'll talk nonsense until you surrender or commit suicide.[/i]
--[[domino (marvel)|Domino]] 

[b]Deadpool[/b] is a mercenary and anti-hero appearing in comic books published by [[marvel|Marvel Comics]]. Created by artist Rob Liefeld and writer Fabian Nicieza, Deadpool (Wade Wilson) first appeared in [i]The New Mutants[/i] #98 (Feb. 1991).

A disfigured and mentally unstable mercenary with the ability to quickly regenerate himself, Deadpool originally appeared as a villain in an issue of [i]New Mutants[/i], and later in issues of [i]X-Force[/i]. The character has since starred in several ongoing series, and shares titles with other characters such as [[cable (marvel)|Cable]]. The character, known as the "Merc with a Mouth", is famous for his talkative nature and his tendency to "break the [[fourth wall]]", which is used by writers for humorous effect.

With his inclusion in [[Marvel vs. Capcom 3|Marvel vs. Capcom 3]] his ability to break the fourth wall has been taken to "a whole new level.":http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S66LtJ77mRk The character would later achieve even greater success after his [[deadpool (movie)|2016 film of the same name]], followed up by two sequels, [[Deadpool 2|one in 2018]] and [[Deadpool & Wolverine|another in 2024]].

title: broccodess

Her version of Dejiko's costume is also slightly different, having white stripes on the bows and a blue stripe on the skirt/apron. Instead of the cat hat, she usually wears a maid headdress when disguised as Dejiko.

title: master_gundam
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]GF13-001NHII Master Gundam[/b]

A [[mobile_suit|Mobile Fighter]] created by Neo [[Hong Kong]] for the [[g_gundam|13th Gundam Fight.]] Built to suit the formidable martial artist, [[master asia|the Undefeated of the East, Master Asia]], it was exceptionally agile and powerful. Its arsenal included hand beam cannons and the comical Master Cloth - a beam weapon shaped like Master Asia's belt, used for a variety of purposes due to his versatile and wide-ranged fighting style.

title: melody_pianissima
body:
A portrait ghost to be captured in [i][[Luigi's Mansion]][/i]. 

Known as the [b]Beautiful Pianist[/b], she is a talented musician who excels at playing the [[piano]]. Despite her beauty her personality is quite unpleasant and she is arrogant about her talents. She is a big lover of video games and challenges [[Luigi]] to a trivia game to see if he can correctly identify what classic [[mario (series)|Mario]] tune she is playing.

Her notable trademarks are having [[long_hair|long]] [[blonde hair]], [[ghost|ghostly]] [[blue skin]], [[glowing_eyes|glowing]] [[yellow eyes]] that [[solid_eyes|lack pupils]] and a [[purple dress|purple]] [[long dress|dress]] that has a [[black bow]].

Shivers, another Portrait Ghost roaming the mansion, is madly in love with her.

Called [b]Pian[/b] (ピアン) in Japanese.

title: morinaka_kazaki_(adult)
body:
The 22-year-old alternate version of [[Nijisanji]]'s [[Morinaka Kazaki]], chronologically her 12th and 13th costumes.

The design of her 22-year-old version was teased during her "2021 birthday stream":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8ybM_dVzLa4]. Her 22-year-old's self's 3D model debuted first at her 1st VR LIVE show, Gekokujou (下剋上), in February 2022, before being publicly revealed during her "2022 birthday stream":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UmQWlBmryJU]. She later gained a 2D model on March 15, 2023, one with a different appearance to her 3D version.

In her 2D form, her 22-year-old self has [[long hair|long]] [[green hair|green]] and [[pink hair|pink]] [[gradient hair]] tied in a [[braid]] on her left with a [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon]]. Her default costume consists of a [[black shirt|black]] [[crop top]], a [[black choker]], a [[white jacket]] with a [[bear print]], a [[black skirt]], [[multiple belts|multiple]] [[black belt|black belts]], a [[single thighhigh|single]] [[fishnet thighhighs|fishnet thighhigh]] on her right leg and an [[o-ring]] [[thigh strap]] on her left leg, and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]].

title: animdude
body:
Scott Braden Cawthon (Born June 4, 1978, in Bell County, Texas), also known under the username "Animdude," is an American game developer, author, animator, screenwriter, and film producer who is the creator and original developer of the Five Nights at Freddy's franchise, including the Clickteam era of games, spin-offs, and troll games.

This tag is used for depictions of Scott as a character, most often represented by the character Animdude, whom he uses as his avatar. For his art, see [[Scott Cawthon]].

title: donkey_kong_jr._(game)
body:
The second Donkey Kong arcade game and sequel to [i][[donkey_kong_(1981_game)|Donkey Kong]][/i], released in 1982. 

[[Mario]] has imprisoned [[Donkey Kong]], which prompts his son [[Donkey Kong Jr.]] to set out to save him. A platformer like the previous entry, he must avoid enemies, jump over obstacles and climb vines in order to take the key away from Mario to break his father out of his cage. 

Notable for being one of the few games where Mario is the antagonist.

title: toga_himiko
body:
One of the antagonists from [[Boku no Hero Academia]]. 

She has [[blonde hair]] that she wears done up in a [[messy hair|messy]] [[double bun]] along with [[blunt bangs]] and [[sidelocks]], [[yellow eyes]] that are often [[narrowed_eyes|narrowed]] or with [[sanpaku|tightened irises]] and [[slit pupils]], made up with black [[eyeliner]] or with [[bags_under_eyes|bags under her eyes]]. She frequently [[blush]]es and [[smile]]s baring her teeth that feature prominent [[fangs]]. 

She typically wears a [[serafuku]] with a [[blue sailor collar]] and [[red neckerchief]] with a [[yellow_cardigan|yelllow]] [[cardigan]] sweater over it, and a [[blue_skirt|blue]] [[pleated skirt]].  She also wears [[black_socks|black]] [[kneehighs]] and [[brown_footwear|brown]] [[loafers]].

She carries a [[knife]], and when equipped to fight, she usually wears a [[black_bandana|black]] [[bandana]] [[bandana_over_mouth|over her mouth]] or around her neck printed with [[teeth]], sometimes a [[black_mask|black]] [[mouth mask]], a [[green belt]] with [[belt pouch]]es, [[thigh strap]]s with  [[thigh pouch]]es, and a back mounted [[tank_(container)|]] connected by [[hose]]s to [[canister]]s on her shoulders that act as [[syringe]]s.

Her quirk allows her to [[transformation|transform]] to look like anyone whose [[blood]] she drinks.

Knox":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ronald_Knox, who wrote the famous "Knox Decalogue":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Age_of_Detective_Fiction#Description_of_the_genre, a list of "rules" that mysteries should follow in order to be solvable.

She has [[purple hair]] which is styled into [[drill hair|drills]]. Normally she seems cold and emotionless, but can sometimes become rather terrifying. She is famous for her english catchphrase "Die The death! Sentence to death! Great equalizer is The Death!!"

[b]FLCL[/b] (Furi Kuri, pronounced in English as Fooly Cooly) is a [[science fiction]] and comedy OVA series written by Yōji Enokido, directed by [[Tsurumaki Kazuya|]] and produced by the FLCL Production Committee, which included [[Gainax]], Production I.G, and Starchild Records. It was released in April 26, 2000.

FLCL follows Nandaba Naota, a twelve-year-old boy living in the fictional Japanese suburb of Mabase, and his interactions with Haruhara Haruko, who arrives in the quiet suburb, drawn by the industrial town houses and the Medical Mechanica building.

title: luigi's_mansion
body:
A subseries in the [[Mario_(series)|Mario]] franchise, starring [[Luigi]] as the main character. In the game, Luigi goes through a haunted mansion to rescue [[Mario]] - who is trapped in a painting by [[King Boo]] - by using a vacuum cleaner called the [[Poltergust 3000]], which is used to catch [[ghost|ghosts]]. 

h4. Games

* [b]Luigi's Mansion[/b]: The original game for the Nintendo [[Gamecube]] released in 2001, featuring the [[Poltergust 3000]], and the infamous Mansion known across the franchise.
* [b][[Luigi's Mansion: Dark Moon|Luigi's Mansion 2]][/b] ([b]Dark Moon[/b] in America): The [[Nintendo 3DS]] sequel released in 2013, now going through a mission-based storyline across 5 new mansions and the debut of the [[Poltergust 5000]].
* [b]Luigi's Mansion Arcade[/b]: The [[arcade_cabinet |arcade]] game released in 2015. A [[light gun]] shooter based on Luigi's Mansion: Dark Moon, featuring much of the same locations, enemies and story.
* [b]Luigi's Mansion 3DS[/b]: A 3DS remake of the original Gamecube game in 2018, including all the original mechanics as well as improved graphics and the debut of [[Gooigi]].
* [b][[Luigi's Mansion 3]][/b]: A Halloween 2019 release, taking the setting inside a Haunted Hotel, and introducing the [[Poltergust G-00]], further introducing Gooigi as a major mechanic in the game.

h4. See also

* [[Princess King Boo]]

title: tate_eboshi
body:
A tate-eboshi (立烏帽子, lit. "standing eboshi cap") is a tall, straight hat worn by Japanese male aristocrats since the "Heian Period":[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heian_period]. Afterwards, various types of eboshi were born, e.g. [i]Kazaori eboshi (Samurai eboshi), Okina eboshi[/i], etc. [i]Tate eboshi[/i] is the best-known one. This headdress came about in the "Heian period":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heian_period based on headgear known as a [i]hashiha-kouburi[/i] (圭冠).

Kanmuri are official hats worn in the imperial court and eboshi are casual headdresses worn by the nobility and it was also worn by the normal people. The Mikado never uses an eboshi. [b]Danbooru currently does not distinguish [i]eboshi[/i] from ancient Japanese [i]kanmuri[/i] (冠).[/b]

Physically, the kanmuri stands out thanks to the "koji (巾子)", a cylindrical shape that stands upright from the top of the headwear, and the "ei (纓)", string-shaped cloth which hangs down from the rear of the headwear towards the wearer's back. The Japanese at the time when kanmuri were still simple sack-like shapes had a topknot on their head. They wore kanmuri by putting the topknot through a tube and binding the root of the topknot wearing this sack and letting the rest of the string hang down their backs. The terms "koji" and "ei", which were used even when the shape and quality of the kanmuri changed, serve as a reminder of this older form. 

Notably worn by [[Mononobe no Futo]] and [[Soga no Tojiko]] of the [[Touhou]] series.

h4. See also

* [[hina ningyou]]
* [[Tag Group:Attire]]
* For a legendary figure, nicknamed "Tate Eboshi", see [[Suzuka Gozen]].

h4. External links

* "Noh Terminology: 'Eboshi'":http://db2.the-noh.com/edic/2009/02/eboshi.html 
* "Tangorin":http://tangorin.com/general/%E7%83%8F%E5%B8%BD%E5%AD%90 
* "Wikimedia Commons":http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Yasaka-jinja_01.jpg

title: the_lego_batman_movie
body: The Lego Batman Movie is a 2017 animated superhero comedy film, based on characters created by [[DC Comics]] and the Lego Batman toy line. It was directed by Chris McKay (in his feature directorial debut) from a screenplay that is based on a Seth Grahame-Smith story. The film is a collaboration between production houses from the United States, Australia, and Denmark, the first spin-off in [[The Lego Movie]] franchise and the second installment overall. The film features Will Arnett reprising his role as Batman from The Lego Movie alongside Zach Galifianakis, Michael Cera, Rosario Dawson, and Ralph Fiennes. The story follows Batman as he attempts to overcome his greatest fear while saving Gotham City from the Joker's latest scheme.

[[Paul Rudd]], Romany Malco, and Seth Rogen play co-workers who resolve to help him lose his virginity, and Catherine Keener stars as Andy's love interest, Trish.

title: tracer_(overwatch)
body:
[i]"Cheers, love!  The cavalry's here!"[/i]

Real Name: Lena Oxton
Age: 26
Occupation: Adventurer
Country: England

An offense-class character in [[Overwatch]]. Lena Oxton (call sign: "Tracer") was handpicked to test the prototype of a teleporting fighter, the Slipstream. During its flight, the aircraft malfunctioned and disappeared. Lena was presumed dead. Months later she reappeared, but her molecules had desynchronized from the flow of time and she would disappear from the present on occasion. A scientist by the name of [[winston_(overwatch)|Winston]] developed a chronal accelerator for her to anchor herself to the present, and control her flow of time at will.

In "Reflections", Tracer was shown together with her [[yuri|girlfriend]] [[emily (overwatch)|Emily]].

The story follows [[Puss in Boots (shrek)|]], who teams up with [[Kitty Softpaws]] and [[Perrito (puss in boots)|]] to find the Last Wish of the fallen Wishing Star to restore eight of his nine lives. title: victorious
body:
Victorious is a teen musical sitcom created by Dan Schneider, which aired on [[Nickelodeon]] from 2010–13.

The star of the show is Tori Vega (Victoria Justice), who gets into Hollywood Arts (a school for the arts in Hollywood) after filling in for her less-talented sister Trina (Daniella Monet) during a big showcase. Backing her up throughout the experience is André Harris (Leon Thomas III), a musically gifted boy who almost immediately warms up to her. On the flip-side, there's Jade West (Elizabeth Gillies), a dark-natured girl acting as Tori's rival. Completing the cast are [[Cat Valentine|Caterina "Cat" Valentine]] ([[Ariana Grande]]), a hypersensitive girl on her own level of reality; Robbie Shapiro (Matt Bennett), an awkward and shy guy who is rarely seen without his puppet Rex Powers; and Beck Oliver (Avan Jogia), Jade's much more mellow significant other.

title: stalker_(game)
body:
Stalker (stylized S.T.A.L.K.E.R.) is a [[video game]] series produced by the Ukrainian company GSC Game World, set in the exclusion zone around [[chernobyl npp|Chornobyl Nuclear Power Plant]] and inspired by the 1979 Soviet movie [[Stalker (1979)|of the same name]]. The first 3 games in the series (Shadow of Chernobyl, Clear Sky, Call of Pripyat) were released within 1 year of each other and are often discussed as a single extended game. The first true sequel, [[stalker 2: heart of chornobyl|S.T.A.L.K.E.R. 2: Heart of Chornobyl]], released on November 20th, 2024 (a gap of 15 years between releases).

h4. External links
* https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S.T.A.L.K.E.R
* http://stalker.wikia.com

title: president_(sonic)
body:
The unnamed sitting President of the [[Sonic (series)|]] series' equivalent of the [[United States]]. He first appeared in [[Sonic Adventure 2]], facing [[Dr. Eggman]]'s threat of world destruction.
In [[Shadow the Hedgehog (game)|]], he leads the planet's resistance against the invasion of [[Black Doom]]'s army. He notably keeps a photo of [[sonic_the_hedgehog|Sonic]] and [[shadow_the_hedgehog|Shadow]] posing in front of the [[White House]] on his desk, as he regards them as heroes.

title: mephistopheles_(project_moon)
body:
A [[bus]] with a [[Steam Locomotive|Steam]] [[Locomotive]]-like  exterior that serves as the Sinners' mode of transport and living quarters.
Its engine was developed by [[Faust (project moon)|]], and its mirror technology (which allows access to the many ingame alternate identities) was partially developed by [[Yi Sang (project moon)|]].

It is operated by [[Charon (project moon)|]], who calls it Mephi.

In literature, Mephistopheles is the demon that offers the doctor Faust vast knowledge in exchange for his soul.

title: yue_ying_(shin_sangoku_musou)
body:
[[Shin Sangoku Musou]]/Dynasty Warriors's portrayal of Lady Huang, [[Zhuge Liang]]'s wife.

Her classic appearance makes her clothed in armor and gives her dark auburn hair, as an homage to the challenge she gave to her suitors in folklore (she claimed she was ugly, that she had tanned skin, red hair...), and she is armed with a dagger-axe or "ge".

Her modern appearance varies between games. Her early appearance in [i][[Shin Sangoku Musou 5]][/i] gives her a lighter red hair color, somewhat tanned skin, a facial mark and she is armed either with a bow or a crossbow/dagger gauntlet weapon (termed the "blade bow") that she presumably invented.

Her later appearances toned down her hair color (now a light auburn) and her skin color. In [i][[Shin Sangoku Musou 6]][/i], she is armed either with a staff or her classic dagger-axe. In [i][[Shin Sangoku Musou 7|7]][/i], it's either her dagger-axe or the blade bow.

Regardless, she is always portrayed as a brilliant inventor. The wood oxen, the juggernauts and the various animal-like weapons she spawns in her musous all came from her inventive mind in the games.

title: hank_pym
body: Dr. Henry Jonathan Pym is a character appearing in American comic books published by [[marvel|Marvel Comics]]. Created by penciller Jack Kirby, editor-plotter Stan Lee and writer Larry Lieber, Pym debuted in Tales to Astonish #27 (January 1962). He returned several issues later as the original iteration of [[Ant-Man]], a superhero with the power to shrink to the size of an ant. He later assumed other superhero identities, including the size-changing Giant-Man and Goliath; the insect-themed Yellowjacket; and briefly, the Wasp. He is a founding member of [[Avengers (series)|the Avengers]] superhero team, and the creator of the robotic villain [[Ultron]]. He is also the ex-husband of [[Janet van Dyne]] and the father of Nadia van Dyne, his daughter by his first wife, Maria Pym.

title: cruz_azul
body: Club de Futbol Cruz Azul, commonly referred to as Cruz Azul, is a professional football club based in [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]. It competes in the [[Liga MX]], the top tier of Mexican football. Founded in 1927 in Jasso, Hidalgo, the club officially moved to Mexico City in 1971, where it had already registered a great presence and activity since its beginnings. Estadio Azteca, the nation's largest sports venue, served as their home venue until 1996, when they moved to the Estadio Ciudad de los Deportes, which was renamed Estadio Azul. After 22 years, the team returned to the Azteca following the conclusion of the 2017–18 Liga MX season. Its headquarters are in La Noria, a suburb within [[Xochimilco]] in the southern part of Mexico City.

title: ghetsis_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Ghetsis Harmonia Gropius[/b], known as [b]G-Cis Harmonia Gropius[/b] (ゲーチス・ハルモニア・グロピウス) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon bw|Black and White]][/i].

The mastermind behind Team Plasma and its true leader. He is a cold and calculating master manipulator who once tried to use N to take over the world [tn](official bio)[/tn]. 

He has [[red eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[green hair]] with an [[ahoge]]. In his [[pokemon bw2|BW2]] outfit, he wears a [[red-tinted eyewear|red]] [[eyepiece]] over his right eye, a [[high collar]] [[cloak]], two [[gold bracelet|gold]] [[bracelet|bracelets]], and carries a [[cane]] with the Team Plasma [[logo]] on it.

h4. Official Art

title: donkey_kong_3
body:
The third game in the [i][[donkey_kong_(series)|Donkey Kong series]][/i] and the final Donkey Kong arcade game, released in 1983. Unlike [[donkey_kong_(1981_game)|Donkey Kong]] and [[donkey_kong_jr._(game)|Donkey Kong Jr.]] this game is not a platformer, but something more akin to a "Shoot 'em Up". With your bug sprayer you must chase away [[Donkey Kong]] and the bugs in order to protect your flowers in the greenhouse. 

Notable for being the only game in the Donkey Kong arcade series to not feature [[Mario]]. Instead the game's protagonist is [[stanley_(donkey_kong)|Stanley]], the character from the 1982 [[Game & Watch]] title [i]Greenhouse[/i] of which Donkey Kong 3 is based on.

title: mario_vs._donkey_kong_2:_march_of_the_minis
body:
Sequel to [[Mario vs. Donkey Kong]], released on the [[Nintendo DS]]. Unlike the previous entry, it forgoes the ability to directly control [[Mario]] and the platforming gameplay in order for the player to guide the [[Mini-Mario|Mini-Marios]] to puzzle solve through stages full of obstacles  with the [[touchscreen|touch screen]] instead.

This entry is notable for revitalizing [[Pauline_(mario)|Pauline]], bringing her back into the Mario franchise and intertwining her again in the Mario & [[Donkey Kong]] rivalry after a 12 year absence, reprising her role as the kidnapped damsel in distress. She still keeps her redesign that she received from [[donkey_kong_(game_boy)|Donkey Kong (Game Boy)]] relatively unchanged.

title: hasaera_rabi
body:
A boss character in [[Toushin Toshi II]] and its remake, [[Toushin Toshi Girls Gift]].

In the original game, Hasaera Rabi is a strict, hot-blooded [[angel]] knight who holds borderline xenophobic views of her enemies, but uses her hot blooded nature to disguise her truly cowardly nature. In Girl's Gift, however, her character is modified. While she is still an Angel Knight, she is far more calm and rational than her original counterpart, but still hides a cowardly nature beneath the surface. She also now possesses the epithet "Blade Angel," after the sword she wields in battle.

In the original game, she has [[long hair|long]], [[pink hair]] and [[green eyes]], with a [[circlet]] around her forehead. She possesses a pair of [[angel wings]] and wears a [[green shirt]] with a [[green skirt]], with a gap exposing her midriff. In Girls Gift, her design is drastically changed to give her [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]], with her [[hair over one eye]]. She now wears blue [[elbow gloves]] and a [[halterneck]], and her top exposes far more [[cleavage]].

body:

The most mysterious member of the Phantom Thieves. Childlike in height, his appearance imitates that of [[Morgana (cat) (Persona 5)|a black cat]], but his true identity is completely unknown. It looks like he's wearing something on his head, but…? That is all the information we currently have. It looks like the black cat is often seen going around with the [[amamiya ren|protagonist]].

Just like the [[amamiya ren|protagonist]], he is a 16-year-old, second-year student at Shujin High School. He stands out with his wild behavior and seems to be a "problem child" even within the school. title: the_shape_of_water
body: The Shape of Water is a 2017 romantic fantasy film directed and produced by [[Guillermo del Toro]], who co-wrote the screenplay with Vanessa Taylor. It stars Sally Hawkins, Michael Shannon, Richard Jenkins, Doug Jones, Michael Stuhlbarg, and Octavia Spencer. Set in 1962 Baltimore, Maryland, the film follows a mute cleaner at a high-security government laboratory who falls in love with a captured humanoid amphibian creature and decides to help him escape from death at the hands of an evil colonel. Filming took place on location in Ontario, Canada, from August to November 2016.

title: light_cruiser_princess
body:
A boss-tier special enemy character in [[Kantai Collection]]. 

Like many [[abyssal ship]]s, she has [[pale skin]], and [[long_hair|long]] [[black hair]]. Unlike most Abyssals, she notably has [[parted bangs]], and an all-black version of the [[dress]], [[boots]] and [[elbow gloves]] that a [i][[Sendai (kancolle)|Sendai]][/i]-class would wear, replete with single-[[cannon]] [[ship turret|turrets]], although her left arm is dominated by a large toothy maw bearing [[torpedo]] launchers and a glowing orb.  Another salient point is that she wears a bondage-style [[blindfold]] over her eyes with two curly [[horns]] sticking out of them.

The character design is an unmistakable reference to [[Jintsuu (kancolle)|Jintsuu]], and considering the event, is a reference to the IJN [i]Jintsuu[/i]'s sinking in the "Battle of Kolombangara":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Kolombangara], where [i]Jintsuu[/i] remained behind to let the destroyers escape, winding up being completely destroyed (split in half by torpedoes) by the Allied attack force.

title: hatakaze_(kancolle)
body:
Hatakaze (旗風, lit. "flag wind") is the fifth of the nine [[kamikaze (kancolle)|Kamikaze]]-class destroyers as represented in [[Kantai Collection]]. 

h4. Appearance

Similar to her sister-ships, she wears a [[Meiji schoolgirl uniform]] with a loose gold [[haori]] over a white [[kimono]] top along dark grey-blue [[hakama short skirt]] tied with a sash bearing an [[anchor]] on the end, and [[brown footwear|brown]], [[lace-up boots|laced]], [[knee_boots|knee-high]], leather [[high heel boots|high-heeled]] [[boots]]. She has [[blue eyes|sky blue]] [[tareme]] eyes and [[blonde_hair|dirty blonde]]/[[brown_hair|brown]] [[drill hair]] with [[hair_between_eyes|bangs that come between her eyes]] in front and a medium-length [[ponytail]] held with a [[red_ribbon|red]] [[hair ribbon]] and mast-themed [[hair ornament]] in back.

Her [[machinery|rigging]] includes a [[smokestack|funnel]] attached to her back with an adjoining mast and two twin-tube [[torpedo]] launchers on either side of the funnel. Further out to the sides, at thigh-level, are cutoff-ship-deck-like platforms that bear a single-[[cannon]] [[ship turret|turret]].  She also carries a single-cannon turret in her left hand like a pistol, which is modeled like a ship's bow in her left hand.

h4. Personality

Hatakaze has a polite, elegant, humble, and mature personality type that resembles the "Yamato Nadeshiko" ideal. Her official voiced lines involve many references about looking up to her older sister-ships, such as Kamikaze, or commenting on [[asakaze (kancolle)|Asakaze's]] night-aversion or [[harukaze (kancolle)|Harukaze's]] cooking.

h4. History

The historical IJN [i]Hatakaze[/i] was launched on March 15th, 1924. At the time of the Battle of Pearl Harbor, she was assigned to Destroyer Division 5 (alongside sister-ships Harukaze, Asakaze, and Matsukaze). Destroyer Division 5 took part as escorts or screens in many of the early South Pacific invasions of the war, including the invasion of the Philippines and Solomon Islands. During the latter of which, [i]Hatakaze[/i] participated in the "Battle of Sunda Straight":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Sunda_Strait], performing a torpedo attack against ABDA cruisers.

On the 2nd of March, 1943, [i]Hatakaze[/i] suffered an accidental explosion, and was forced to receive repairs for over a year, emerging in October of the following year. Following the dissolution of Destroyer Division 5, she was put directly into the Combined Fleet. On January 15th, 1945, she was sunk at port in what is now "Kaohsiung, Taiwan":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaohsiung] by Allied aircraft.

h4. [i]Kamikaze[/i]-class Destroyers
* [[Kamikaze (kancolle)|]] - first Kamikaze-class destroyer
* [[Asakaze (kancolle)|]] - second Kamikaze-class destroyer
* [[Harukaze (kancolle)|]] - third Kamikaze-class destroyer
* [[Matsukaze (kancolle)|]] - fourth Kamikaze-class destroyer
* [b]Hatakaze[/b]

h4. See also

title: destroyer_water_oni
body:
A special boss-type enemy in [[Kantai Collection]], introduced in the Fall 2015 event, centered around the "Solomon Islands Campaign":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solomon_Islands_campaign].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]], [[pale skin]], and orangish-[[red eyes]]. She has what looks like half an [[abyssal ship]] destroyer on her head with glowing eyes worn like a hat.  Underneath the [[teeth]], she is wearing shreds of a [[black serafuku]] on top, and black [[boots]] and [[gloves]]. On her back is a hip-mounted abyssal variation of destroyer [[rigging]], with two large black arms bearing twin-[[cannon]] [[ship turret|turret]].

She notably holds a blue [[tasuki]], similar to the one [[Kaga (kancolle)|Kaga]] wears.

She is likely an homage to the destroyers sunk in the "Battle of Vella Gulf":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Vella_Gulf], where four IJN destroyers, [i][[Hagikaze (kancolle)|Hagikaze]][/i], [i][[Arashi (kancolle)|Arashi]][/i], [i][[Shigure (kancolle)|Shigure]][/i], and [i][[Kawakaze (kancolle)|Kawakaze]][/i], were completely surprised by an American force of six destroyers in the middle of the night due to Americans using radar on their destroyers, while the Japanese did not (this being one of the first times the Japanese used destroyers on their own without a cruiser leader). The battle was a disastrous rout for the Japanese, with the Americans destroying all but [i]Shigure[/i] and never receiving any return fire, and afterwards, the Japanese gave up even trying to resupply their Solomon Island bases with destroyers, significantly hastening Japan's bloody retreat in the Solomon Island Campaign. 

Destroyer Water Demon may be a corrupt reflection of the merger of the three sunken destroyers, like [[Light Cruiser Oni]], or may simply be [[Hagikaze (kancolle)|Hagikaze]], alone, whose [[side ponytail]] is not easily distinguishable, considering the visible tie to [[Kaga (kancolle)|Kaga]].

title: matsukaze_(kancolle)
body:
Matsukaze (松風, lit. "Pine Wind") is fourth of the nine [[Kamikaze (kancolle)|]]-class destroyers in [[Kantai Collection]]. 
Character design by [[Parsley-F]], voiced by [[Itou Shizuka]].

h4. Appearance

Similar to her sister-ships, she wears a [[Meiji schoolgirl uniform]] with a white [[furisode]] top along with a dark green [[hakama skirt]] tied with a sash bearing an [[anchor]] on the end, and [[knee_boots|knee-high]] [[lace-up boots]]. She has [[green eyes|green]] [[tsurime]] eyes and [[short_hair|short]], [[wavy_hair|wavy]] [[black hair]] with [[swept bangs]] in front and a short cow-lick [[ahoge]] up top. She also wears a [[mini top hat]] tilted to the right side of her head.

Her [[machinery|rigging]] includes a [[smokestack|funnel]] attached to her back with an adjoining mast and two twin-tube [[torpedo]] launchers on either side of the funnel. Further out to the sides, at thigh-level, are cutoff-ship-deck-like platforms that bear a single-[[cannon]] [[ship turret|turret]]. She also carries a single-cannon turret in her left hand like a pistol, which is modeled like a ship's bow.

h4. Personality

Matsukaze has a confident, competitive, and tomboyish (and refers to herself with the boyish "boku", similar to [[hatsuzuki (kancolle)|Hatsuzuki]], among others), but also fairly warm personality. Unlike some of her sisters, she's not afraid of the night, and in her hourlies, greets them in the morning.

h4. History

The historical IJN [i]Matsukaze[/i] was launched October 30th, 1923. At the time of The Battle of Pearl Harbor, she was assigned to Destroyer Division 5 (alongside sister-ships [[Harukaze (kancolle)|]] and [[Asakaze (kancolle)|]]). As one of the more obsolete classes of destroyers, her early-war career was spent escorting troop transports for invasions, although in the Battle of Sunda Straight, she helped sink an auxiliary minesweeper.

Throughout the middle of the war (1943-1944), [i]Matsukaze[/i] was engaged in "Tokyo Express" expeditions. [i]Matsukaze[/i] was at Truk during Operation Hailstone, but survived with no direct hits from major ordinance. Later in the year, while escorting a convoy near Saipan, [i]Matsukaze[/i] was struck by a torpedo from the USS [i]Sailfish[/i] and sank on August 25th, 1944.

h4. Trivia

Her boyish character, androgynous appearance and Taisho-era clothing have drawn comparisons with "Takarazuka Revue":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Takarazuka_Revue and the otokoyaku role.
